In a duplicate group, a non-reference image that was pulled in indirectly (a "passenger") now shows its similarity to the group's reference with a trailing star (e.g. 75*%) — the same reference every other row is measured against, so the Similarity column is comparable across rows — and hovering reveals the file it is actually most similar to ("97% similar to <name>"). The bare "—" is now reserved for a passenger with no comparable hash (a Live Photo's video) (#536).
